<hl>
<seg id=1> Mr. Fei Xiaotong was given the Magsaysay Award </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Manila, August 31, (Xinhua News Agency) Notable Chinese sociologist, vice chairman of the Standing Committee of NPC, Fei Xiaotong was given the Magsaysay Award to "Community Leaders" here this afternoon. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The awarding ceremony was held at the Philippine Cultural Center. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Philippine President Ramos attended the ceremony and awarded medals, cash prize and certificates to the 6 preeminent figures. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Mr. Fei Xiaotong said in his appreciation speech, "I will never fail the encouragement from the friendly neighboring country. No matter how much time I could use in the future, I decide to cautiously and conscientiously use every minute left to try my best to do some good matters that serve the interests of the Asian people and even the people throughout the world, and make the knowledge accumulated by the man kind push the society to a nicer one. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Ramon Magsaysay award that is named after a former Philippine president is called the Nobel Prize of Asia. </seg>
<seg id=7> It has 5 awards and is given once a year to figures and organizations with preeminent contributions in the fields of governmental services, public services, community lead, media, literature and creative communication art and international understanding. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Since the Award was established in 1958, 172 individuals and 14 organizations have been given this award. </seg>
</p>
